programme.title: Live International T20 Cricket
programme.sub-title: New Zealand v England: Trans-Tasman Tri-Series - Sixth Match.
programme.desc: New Zealand v England. Coverage of the sixth and penultimate match of the T20 Trans-Tasman Tri-Series, held at Seddon Park in Hamilton. The tourists are staying on in New Zealand following the conclusion of this series, with the first of five one-day internationals against the Black Caps taking place on this ground in a week's time. A two-match Test series then takes place at Eden Park, Auckland and the Hagley Oval in Christchurch, before England return home to prepare for summer Tests with Pakistan and India

programme.sub-title: Jacksonville Jaguars at New England Patriots
programme.desc: Jacksonville Jaguars at New England Patriots in the AFC championship game. From Gillette Stadium. Bill Belichick's Pats are in their seventh straight AFC title game and are 7-4 in the game since Jacksonville's last appearance 18 years ago. programme.title: NFL Playoff: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.sub-title: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.desc: New Orleans Saints (12-5) at Minnesota Vikings (13-3) in an NFC Divisional game. From U.S. Bank Stadium. Mike Zimmer's Vikings opened 2017 with a 29-19 win over New Orleans, keeping QB Drew Brees and Co. out of the end zone until the last two minutes. Everson Griffen and Xavier Rhodes head Minnesota's defense, while the Saints boast a Pro Bowl RB tandem in Alvin Kamara and Mark Ingram. The Vikes' last playoff win was eight years ago, followed by an NFC title-game loss to the Saints. (cc)

programme.title: Super Bowl LII: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New England Patriots
programme.sub-title: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New England Patriots
programme.desc: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New England Patriots at U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, which last hosted in 1992. Justin Timberlake performs at halftime. Bill Belichick's Patriots bid for a record-tying sixth Super Bowl win, while Philly chases its first, having last appeared 13 years ago in a 24-21 loss to New England. Deion Branch was MVP of that game, with QB Tom Brady taking MVP honors in the other four Pats wins. Tight ends Rob Gronkowski (Pats) and Zach Ertz (Eagles) are key scoring threats. (cc)
